      <div xml:id="NA317-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu tōḻi talaimakaṉai varaivu kaṭāyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante urged HIM for marriage.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA317">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            nīṭiruñ cilampiṟ piṭiyoṭu puṇarnta</l>
<l>            pūmpoṟi yorutta lēntukaik kaṭuppat</l>
<l>            tōṭutalai vāṅkiya nīṭukuraṟ paintiṉai</l>
<l>            pavaḷac cevvāyp paiṅkiḷi kavaru</l>
<l>            muyarvarai nāṭanī nayantōḷ kēṇmai</l>
<l>            yaṉṉai yaṟikuva ḷāyiṟ paṉikalan</l>
<l>            teṉṉā kuvako ṟāṉē yentai</l>
<l>            yōṅkuvaraic cāraṟ ṟīñcuṉai yāṭi</l>
<l>            yāyamoṭu kuṟṟa kuvaḷai</l>
<l>            māyitaḻ māmalar puraiiya kaṇṇē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>O man from the land of high mountains,</l>
<l rend="indent">where the green parrot with a coral-red beak seizes</l>
<l rend="indent3">the fresh millet with lengthening ears bending the heads to [their] leaves,</l>
<l rend="indent3">resembling the raised trunk of the flower-dotted male [elephant]</l>
<l rend="indent">united with [its] female on the long big mountain side,</l>
<l rend="indent">if mother should know of [your] intimacy with her you longed for,</l>
<l>what will become of them<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">tāṉ</term>: here we are faced with a problem. There is also a reading <term xml:lang="ta">tām</term>, but this is clearly the lectio facilior. Do we see here the first traces of the emphatic particle, T.V.G.’s expletive?</note>, mingling with dew,</l>
<l>– the eyes that resembled the big blossoms with dark petals</l>
<l rend="indent">of the blue waterlilies plucked with the companions,</l>
<l rend="indent">playing in the sweet mountain spring on the slope of my father’s</l>
<l rend="indent3">high mountain.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
